Part 1, Step 3 (Similarity Scores)

Load and clean data

names(data)[35] <- "YWL_OML"

Graphing results

Organize data

data_mean <- data %>%
  summarize_at(vars(OW_YW:OML_YML), mean)

data_sd <- data %>%
  summarize_at(vars(OW_YW:OML_YML), sd)

data_graph <- data.frame(t(rbind(data_mean, data_sd)))
names(data_graph) <- c("mean", "SD")

data_graph$SE <- data_graph$SD/sqrt(nrow(data))
data_graph$LCI <- data_graph$mean - 1.96*data_graph$SE
data_graph$UCI <- data_graph$mean + 1.96*data_graph$SE
data_graph$Comparison <- row.names(data_graph)

data_graph$Comparison <- fct_inorder(data_graph$Comparison)

data_graph$AgeGender <- c("Old Woman\nYoung Woman", "Old Woman\nOld Man", "Old Woman\nYoung Man",
                          "Young Woman\nOld Man", "Young Woman\nYoung Man", "Old Man\nYoung Man",
                          "Old Woman\nYoung Woman", "Old Woman\nOld Man", "Old Woman\nYoung Man",
                          "Young Woman\nOld Man", "Young Woman\nYoung Man", "Old Man\nYoung Man")

data_graph$AgeGender <- fct_inorder(data_graph$AgeGender)

data_graph_labels <- c("Old Woman\nYoung Woman", "Old Woman\nOld Man", "Old Woman\nYoung Man",
                          "Young Woman\nOld Man", "Young Woman\nYoung Man", "Old Man\nYoung Man")

data_graph$Occupation <- ifelse(str_detect(data_graph$Comparison, "L") == TRUE, "Librarian", "No Occupation")

Create graph of similarity scores

sim_graph <- ggplot(data_graph, aes(group = Occupation, x = AgeGender, y = mean, ymin = LCI, ymax = UCI, color = Occupation)) +
  geom_errorbar(width=0,cex=1, position = position_dodge(width = .3)) +
  geom_point(size=2.5, position = position_dodge(width = .3)) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(legend.position = "none",
        panel.grid.major.x = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor.y = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor.x = element_blank(),
        axis.text.x = element_text(size=15),
        axis.text.y = element_text(size=14),
        axis.title.x = element_blank(),
        axis.title.y = element_text(size=16)) +
  scale_x_discrete(labels=data_graph_labels) +
  ylab("Mean Similarity Score") +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks=c(3.5, 4, 4.5, 5, 5.5), limits=c(3.4, 5.6)) +
  scale_color_manual(values=c("indianred1", "royalblue3"))

Creating tidy summaries of t-tests for graphing difference scores

ttest_graph <- rbind(tidy(Test1), tidy(Test2), tidy(Test3), tidy(Test4), tidy(Test5), tidy(Test6))

ttest_graph$Comparison <- c("Old Woman\nYoung Woman", "Old Woman\nOld Man", "Old Woman\nYoung Man",
                          "Young Woman\nOld Man", "Young Woman\nYoung Man", "Old Man\nYoung Man")

ttest_graph$Comparison <- fct_inorder(ttest_graph$Comparison)

Create graph of difference scores with 95% CIs

diff_graph <- ggplot(ttest_graph, aes(x = Comparison, y = estimate, ymin = conf.low, ymax = conf.high)) +
  geom_errorbar(width=0,cex=1, color="slateblue4") +
  geom_point(size=2.5, color="slateblue4") +
  geom_hline(yintercept=0) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(legend.position = "none",
        panel.grid.major.x = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor.y = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor.x = element_blank(),
        axis.text.x = element_blank(),
        axis.text.y = element_text(size=14),
        axis.title.x = element_blank(),
        axis.title.y = element_text(size=16)) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks=c(0, .5, 1, 1.5), limits=c(-.2, 1.6)) +
  ylab("Difference (With  Without)")

Combine with patchwork

combined_graph <- sim_graph + diff_graph + plot_layout(ncol=1) + plot_annotation(title = "Competence Similarity Scores <span style='color:indianred1;'>With</span> and <span style='color:royalblue3;'>Without</span> Occupation (and Their <span style='color:slateblue4;'>Difference</span>)", theme = theme(plot.title = element_markdown(lineheight = 1.1, size = 18, hjust=.5)))

ggsave("figures/combined_p1.jpg", height=8, width=10, unit="in", dpi=600)
knitr::include_graphics("figures/combined_p1.jpg")
